modules.description: Concatenates a string to each element in a list of strings, modifying the list in place. Operates on strings and lists of strings. Used to prepend or append fixed prefixes or suffixes to multiple file paths during batch processing.

Provides operations for constructing and verifying coherence conditions in ω-categories, including path composition, identity generation, and equivalence checks. Works with structured data types such as globular sets, cells, and higher-dimensional paths. Used to validate complex categorical structures in theoretical computer science and homotopy theory research.

Adds string manipulation capabilities to lists, enabling in-place modification by appending or prepending fixed values to each element. Supports operations on lists of strings and individual strings, ideal for batch file path adjustments. Examples include adding ".txt" to multiple filenames or inserting a directory prefix. No additional functionality provided beyond the first module.
